abstract: >-
  WCI (Web Context Interface) is a three-layer open standard
  that augments standard HTML with structured semantic
  metadata, compresses it into agent-optimised context, and
  provides a typed action protocol — shipped as compact
  modular layers (~2–12 KB minified each).
